ProtectedPortList.name: ProtectedPortList
ProtectedPortList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

VlanList.name: VlanList
VlanList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight vlans, with the first octet specifying vlans 1 through 8, the second octet specifying vlans 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered vlan, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered vlan. Thus, each vlan supported is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then the associated port is in that vlan; the port is not included if the vlans bit has a value of '0'.

Ipv6AddressIfIdentifier.name: Ipv6AddressIfIdentifier

Ipv6IfIndex.name: Ipv6IfIndex
Ipv6IfIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero for each internetwork-layer interface in the managed system. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each internetwork-layer interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

Ipv6IfIndexOrZero.name: Ipv6IfIndexOrZero
Ipv6IfIndexOrZero.description: This textual convention is an extension of the Ipv6IfIndex convention. The latter defines a greater than zero value used to identify an IPv6 interface in the managed system. This extension permits the additional value of zero. The value zero is object-specific and must therefore be defined as part of the description of any object which uses this syntax. Examples of the usage of zero might include situations where interface was unknown, or when none or all interfaces need to be referenced.

PortId.description: This data type is used to model port ids. This is a binary string of 2 octets.

agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThreshold.name: agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThreshold
agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThreshold.description: The CPU Rising utilization threshold in percentage. A zero percent threshold indicates CPU Utilization Notification feature is disabled. A notification is triggered when the total CPU utilization exceeds this threshold over the configured Rising threshold interval. If the Rising threshold is configured to be less than the Falling threshold, the Falling threshold is set equal to the Rising threshold.

agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThresholdInte.name: agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThresholdInterval
agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThresholdInte.description: The CPU Rising threshold interval in seconds. The time interval is configured in multiples of 5 seconds. A zero Rising interval indicates CPU Utilization Notification feature is disabled.

agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThreshold.name: agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThreshold
agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThreshold.description: The CPU Falling utilization threshold in percentage. Configuration of this object value is optional. Value '0' is not allowed for configuration, if the Rising threshold is non-zero. If the Falling threshold is configured to be greater than the Rising threshold, the Rising threshold is set equal to the Falling threshold. If the Falling threshold is not configured, it takes the same value as the Rising threshold. A notification is triggered when the total CPU utilization falls below this threshold over the configured Falling threshold interval.

agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThresholdInt.name: agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThresholdInterval
agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThresholdInt.description: The CPU Falling threshold interval in seconds. Configuration of this object value is optional. Value '0' is not allowed for configuration, if the Rising interval is non-zero. If the Falling interval is not configured, it takes the same value as the Rising interval. The time interval is configured in multiples of 5 seconds.

agentSwitchCpuProcessFreeMemoryThreshold.name: agentSwitchCpuProcessFreeMemoryThreshold
agentSwitchCpuProcessFreeMemoryThreshold.description: The CPU Free Memory threshold in kilobytes. A zero threshold value indicates the CPU Free Memory Notification feature is disabled. Notifications are triggered when the CPU Free Memory falls below the configured threshold and when it rises to 10% above the configured threshold.

agentServicePortIpv6AddressAutoConfig.name: agentServicePortIpv6AddressAutoConfig
agentServicePortIpv6AddressAutoConfig.description: The ipv6 address autoconfig allows the device to perform IPv6 stateless address auto-configuration to discover prefixes on the link and then to add the eui-64 based addresses to the serviceport interface.

agentServicePortIpv6ConfigProtocol.name: agentServicePortIpv6ConfigProtocol
agentServicePortIpv6ConfigProtocol.description: The Service Port.s IPv6 protocol configured on the switch.

agentServicePortDhcp6ClientDuid.name: agentServicePortDhcp6ClientDuid
agentServicePortDhcp6ClientDuid.description: The DHCPv6 Client unique DUID. This value cannot be modified

agentServicePortDhcp6ADVERTISEMessagesRe.name: agentServicePortDhcp6ADVERTISEMessagesReceived
agentServicePortDhcp6ADVERTISEMessagesRe.description: The no. of DHCPv6 messages of type ADVERTISE that have been received by the DHCPv6 client on the service port.

agentServicePortDhcp6REPLYMessagesReceiv.name: agentServicePortDhcp6REPLYMessagesReceived
agentServicePortDhcp6REPLYMessagesReceiv.description: The no. of DHCPv6 messages of type REPLY that have been received by the DHCPv6 client on the service port.

agentServicePortDhcp6ADVERTISEMessagesDi.name: agentServicePortDhcp6ADVERTISEMessagesDiscarded
agentServicePortDhcp6ADVERTISEMessagesDi.description: The no. of DHCPv6 messages of type ADVERTISE that have been discarded by the DHCPv6 client on the service port.

agentServicePortDhcp6REPLYMessagesDiscar.name: agentServicePortDhcp6REPLYMessagesDiscarded
agentServicePortDhcp6REPLYMessagesDiscar.description: The no. of DHCPv6 messages of type REPLY that have been discarded by the DHCPv6 client on the service port.

agentServicePortDhcp6MalformedMessagesRe.name: agentServicePortDhcp6MalformedMessagesReceived
agentServicePortDhcp6MalformedMessagesRe.description: The no. of DHCPv6 messages received malformed by the DHCPv6 client on the service port.

agentServicePortDhcp6SOLICITMessagesSent.name: agentServicePortDhcp6SOLICITMessagesSent
agentServicePortDhcp6SOLICITMessagesSent.description: The no. of DHCPv6 messages of type SOLICIT that have been sent by the DHCPv6 client on the service port.

agentServicePortDhcp6REQUESTMessagesSent.name: agentServicePortDhcp6REQUESTMessagesSent
agentServicePortDhcp6REQUESTMessagesSent.description: The no. of DHCPv6 messages of type REQUEST that have been sent by the DHCPv6 client on the service port.

agentServicePortDhcp6RENEWMessagesSent.name: agentServicePortDhcp6RENEWMessagesSent
agentServicePortDhcp6RENEWMessagesSent.description: The no. of DHCPv6 messages of type RENEW that have been sent by the DHCPv6 client on the service port.

agentServicePortDhcp6REBINDMessagesSent.name: agentServicePortDhcp6REBINDMessagesSent
agentServicePortDhcp6REBINDMessagesSent.description: The no. of DHCPv6 messages of type REBIND that have been sent by the DHCPv6 client on the service port.

agentServicePortDhcp6RELEASEMessagesSent.name: agentServicePortDhcp6RELEASEMessagesSent
agentServicePortDhcp6RELEASEMessagesSent.description: The no. of DHCPv6 messages of type RELEASE that have been sent by the DHCPv6 client on the service port.

agentServicePortDhcp6StatsReset.name: agentServicePortDhcp6StatsReset
agentServicePortDhcp6StatsReset.description: Clear the DHCPv6 Client statistics on the service port. A value of reset(1) is used to reset the statistics. A read on this object will always return the value none(0). The value none(0) cannot be forcibly set by the administrator.

agentSnmpLinkUpDownTrapFlag.name: agentSnmpLinkUpDownTrapFlag
agentSnmpLinkUpDownTrapFlag.description: Link Up/Down Flag - Enable/Disable Link Up/Link Down traps for the entire switch. When set to Enable, the Link Up/Down traps will be sent only if the Link Trap flag setting associated with the port (Port Configuration Menu) is set to Enable.

agentSnmpMultipleUsersTrapFlag.name: agentSnmpMultipleUsersTrapFlag
agentSnmpMultipleUsersTrapFlag.description: Multiple Users Flag - Enable/Disable Multiple User traps. When the value is set to Enable, a Multiple User Trap is sent whenever someone logs in to the terminal interface (EIA 232 or Telnet) and there is already an existing terminal interface session.

agentSnmpSpanningTreeTrapFlag.name: agentSnmpSpanningTreeTrapFlag
agentSnmpSpanningTreeTrapFlag.description: Spanning Tree Flag - This flag enables the sending of new root traps and topology change notification traps.

agentSnmpBroadcastStormTrapFlag.name: agentSnmpBroadcastStormTrapFlag
agentSnmpBroadcastStormTrapFlag.description: Broadcast Storm Flag - This flag enables or disables the broadcast storm trap. You must also enable Broadcast Storm Recovery Mode (see the Switch Configuration Menu). When this value is set to Enable and Broadcast Storm Recovery mode is set to Enable, the Broadcast Storm Start/End traps are sent when the switch enters and leaves Broadcast Storm Recovery.

agentSnmpCpuTresholdTrapFlag.name: agentSnmpCpuTresholdTrapFlag
agentSnmpCpuTresholdTrapFlag.description: Enables sending of a trap on the CPU occupancy exceeding the rising threshold.

agentSnmpBuffersTrapFlag.name: agentSnmpBuffersTrapFlag
agentSnmpBuffersTrapFlag.description: Enables sending of a trap on the internal message buffer count exceeding the rising threshold.

agentSpanningTreeMode.name: agentSpanningTreeMode
agentSpanningTreeMode.description: The switch's Spanning Tree Switch Status. This functionality is now handled by agentStpAdminMode

agentBpduGuardMode.name: agentBpduGuardMode
agentBpduGuardMode.description: The spanning tree BPDU Guard Mode. enable(1) - enables BPDU Guard Mode on the switch. disable(2) - disables BPDU Guard Mode on the switch. The default status is disabled. This functionality is now handled by agentStpBpduGuardMode

agentBPDUFilteringMode.name: agentBPDUFilteringMode
agentBPDUFilteringMode.description: The spanning tree BPDU Filter Mode, it enables BPDU Filter on all edge ports. enable(1) - enables BPDU Filter Mode on the switch. disable(2) - disables BPDU Filter Mode on the switch. The default status is disabled. This functionality is now handled by agentStpBpduFilterDefault

agentSwitchFdbAddressAgingTimeout.name: agentSwitchFdbAddressAgingTimeout
agentSwitchFdbAddressAgingTimeout.description: The address aging timeout. Specifies aging time in seconds (10 - 1000000) before a dynamic MAC address is erased from the Filtering Database. The default value is 300 seconds. Use '0' to disable aging time for the MAC address Table.

agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutTable.name: agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutTable
agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutTable.description: The switch's address aging timeout table

agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutEntry.name: agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutEntry
agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutEntry.description: Aging information about a specific Filtering Database.

agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeout.name: agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeout
agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeout.description: The FDB entry's address aging timeout (in seconds).value '0' to disable Aging Timeout feature.

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringTable.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringTable
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringTable.description: The switch's static Mac filtering table

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringEntry.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringEntry
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringEntry.description: Per-port ingress/egress filter configuration based on VLAN Id and MAC address.

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringVlanId.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringVlanId
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringVlanId.description: The Static MAC Filter Vlan Id

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringAddress.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringAddress
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringAddress.description: The Static MAC Filter MAC address

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringSourcePortM.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringSourcePortMask
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringSourcePortM.description: The Static MAC Filter source port mask. When setting this value, the system will ignore configuration for ports not between the first and last valid ports. Configuration of any port numbers between this range that are not valid ports return a failure message, but will still apply configuration for valid ports. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table.

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringDestPortMas.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringDestPortMask
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringDestPortMas.description: The Static MAC Filter destination port mask. When setting this value, the system will ignore configuration for ports not between the first and last valid ports. Configuration of any port numbers between this range that are not valid ports return a failure message, but will still apply configuration for valid ports. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table. Configuring destination port mask for a unicast MAC filter is not supported on some platforms.

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringStatus.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringStatus
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringStatus.description: The Static MAC Filter status. Supported values: active(1) - valid entry createAndGo(4) - used to create a new entry destroy(6) - removes the entry

agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupTable.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupTable
agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast Source Specific Multicast Groups for which there are members on a particular interface and VLAN.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupEntry.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupEntry
agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupTable.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupAddressType.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupAddressType
agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupAddressType.description: The address type of the agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupTable entry. This value applies to both the agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupAddress and the agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupLastReporter entries.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupAddress.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupAddress
agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information. The InetAddressType, e.g. IPv4 or IPv6, is identified by the agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupAddressType variable in the agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroup table.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupIfIndex.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupIfIndex
agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupIfIndex.description: The interface for which this entry contains information for an IP multicast group address.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupVlanId.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupVlanId
agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupVlanId.description: The VLAN for which this entry contains information for an IP multicast group address.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupLastReporter.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupLastReporter
agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupLastReporter.description: The IP address of the source of the last membership report received for this IP Multicast group address on this interface and VLAN. The InetAddressType, e.g. IPv4 or IPv6, is identified by the agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupAddressType variable in the agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroup table.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupSourceFilterMode.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupSourceFilterMode
agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupSourceFilterMode.description: The state in which the interface is currently set. The value indicates the relevance of the corresponding source list entries in the SrcList Table (agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListTable).

agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListTable.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListTable
agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the Source List entries corresponding to each VLAN, interface and SSM multicast group pair on a MGMD Snooping switch.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListEntry.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListEntry
agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListTable.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListAddressType.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListAddressType
agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListAddressType.description: The address type of the InetAddress variables in this table. This value applies to the agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListHostAddress and agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListAddress entries.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListAddress.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListAddress
agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListIfIndex.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListIfIndex
agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListIfIndex.description: The interface for which this entry contains information for an IP multicast group address.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListVlanId.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListVlanId
agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListVlanId.description: The VLAN for which this entry contains information for an IP multicast group address.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListHostAddress.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListHostAddress
agentSwitchSnoopSSMSrcListHostAddress.description: The host address to which this entry corresponds. The agentSwitchSnoopSSMGroupSourceFilterMode value for this Group address, interface and VLAN indicates whether this Host address is included or excluded.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBTable.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBTable
agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBTable.description: MGMD Snooping Source Specific Multicast Forwarding database Table.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBEntry.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBEntry
agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBEntry.description: An entry is created by IGMP Snooping for each group learned in the VLAN.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBVlanIndex.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBVlanIndex
agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN in which the group is learned.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBGroupAddressType.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBGroupAddressType
agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBGroupAddressType.description: This object indicates IP multicast address type learned by MGMD Snooping.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBGroupAddress.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBGroupAddress
agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBGroupAddress.description: This object indicates IP multicast address learned by MGMD Snooping.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBSourceAddress.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBSourceAddress
agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBSourceAddress.description: This object indicates IP Source address learned by MGMD Snooping.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBIncludePortList.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBIncludePortList
agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBIncludePortList.description: This object indicates the set of ports on which MGMD Membership Reports are received for the group indicating interest to receive traffic sent to the group.

agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBExcludePortList.name: agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBExcludePortList
agentSwitchSnoopSSMFDBExcludePortList.description: This object indicates the set of ports on which MGMD Membership Reports are received for the group indicating interest to not to receive traffic sent to the group.

agentSwitchDot3FlowControlMode.name: agentSwitchDot3FlowControlMode
agentSwitchDot3FlowControlMode.description: Config switchconfig flowcontrol allows you to enable or disable 802.3x flow control for the switch. This value applies to only full-duplex mode ports. Enabling asymmetric flow control allows the switch to receive pause frames but it will not transmit pause frames.

agentSwitchBroadcastControlMode.name: agentSwitchBroadcastControlMode
agentSwitchBroadcastControlMode.description: The switch config broadcast allows you to enable or disable broadcast storm recovery mode. When you specify Enable for Broadcast Storm Recovery and the broadcast traffic on any Ethernet port exceeds the configured threshold, the switch blocks (discards) the broadcast traffic.

agentSwitchBroadcastControlThreshold.name: agentSwitchBroadcastControlThreshold
agentSwitchBroadcastControlThreshold.description: Configures the broadcast storm recovery threshold for this port as a percentage of port speed.

agentSwitchBroadcastControlThresholdUnit.name: agentSwitchBroadcastControlThresholdUnit
agentSwitchBroadcastControlThresholdUnit.description: Configures the units of the threshold value to percentage of port speed or absolute packets per second.

agentSwitchMulticastControlMode.name: agentSwitchMulticastControlMode
agentSwitchMulticastControlMode.description: The switch config multicast allows you to enable or disable multicast storm recovery mode. When you specify Enable for multicast Storm Recovery and the multicast traffic on any Ethernet port exceeds the configured threshold, the switch blocks (discards) the multicast traffic.

agentSwitchMulticastControlThreshold.name: agentSwitchMulticastControlThreshold
agentSwitchMulticastControlThreshold.description: Configures the multicast storm recovery threshold for this port as a percentage of port speed.

agentSwitchMulticastControlThresholdUnit.name: agentSwitchMulticastControlThresholdUnit
agentSwitchMulticastControlThresholdUnit.description: Configures the units of the threshold value to percentage of port speed or absolute packets per second.

agentSwitchUnicastControlMode.name: agentSwitchUnicastControlMode
agentSwitchUnicastControlMode.description: The switch config unicast allows you to enable or disable unicast storm recovery mode. When you specify Enable for unicast Storm Recovery and the unknown unicast traffic on any Ethernet port exceeds the configured threshold, the switch blocks (discards) the unknown unicast traffic.

agentSwitchUnicastControlThreshold.name: agentSwitchUnicastControlThreshold
agentSwitchUnicastControlThreshold.description: Configures the unicast storm recovery threshold for this port as a percentage of port speed.

agentSwitchUnicastControlThresholdUnit.name: agentSwitchUnicastControlThresholdUnit
agentSwitchUnicastControlThresholdUnit.description: Configures the units of the threshold value to percentage of port speed or absolute packets per second.

agentSwitchStormControlType.name: agentSwitchStormControlType
agentSwitchStormControlType.description: Type of storm control. broadcast(1) - Broadcast storm control traffic. multicast(2) - Multicast storm control traffic. broadcast(3) - Unicast traffic resulted in destination lookup failure.

agentSwitchStormControlAction.name: agentSwitchStormControlAction
agentSwitchStormControlAction.description: Action to be taken when storm control rate limit is reached. shutdown(1) - Diag disable the interface on storm control. trap(2) - Generate trap on storm control.

agentSwitchSnoopingCfgTable.name: agentSwitchSnoopingCfgTable
agentSwitchSnoopingCfgTable.description: A table of the IGMP/MLD Snooping Global configuration entries.

agentSwitchSnoopingCfgEntry.name: agentSwitchSnoopingCfgEntry
agentSwitchSnoopingCfgEntry.description: Represents entry for Snooping switch Configuration.

agentSwitchSnoopingProtocol.name: agentSwitchSnoopingProtocol
agentSwitchSnoopingProtocol.description: The protocol type of network protocol in use.

agentSwitchSnoopingAdminMode.name: agentSwitchSnoopingAdminMode
agentSwitchSnoopingAdminMode.description: This enables or disables Snooping on the system.

agentSwitchSnoopingPortMask.name: agentSwitchSnoopingPortMask
agentSwitchSnoopingPortMask.description: IGMP/MLD Snooping Port Mask. This allows configuration of IGMP/MLD Snooping on selected ports. IGMP Snooping cannot be enabled on an interface that has routing enabled, or is a member of a LAG. If a port which has IGMP/MLD Snooping enabled becomes enabled for routing, or is enlisted as a member of a LAG, IGMP/MLD Snooping functionality will be disabled on that port. IGMP/MLD Snooping functionality will be subsequently be reenabled if routing is disabled or LAG membership is removed from an interface that had previously had IGMP Snooping enabled. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table.

agentSwitchSnoopingMulticastControlFrame.name: agentSwitchSnoopingMulticastControlFramesProcessed
agentSwitchSnoopingMulticastControlFrame.description: Multicast Control Frames Processed by CPU. The number of multicast control frames that have been processed by the CPU.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanTable.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanTable
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanTable.description: A table of the IGMP/MLD Snooping Vlan configuration entries.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanEntry.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanEntry
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanEntry.description: Represents entry for a IGMP/MLD Snooping Vlan.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanAdminMode.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanAdminMode
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanAdminMode.description: This enables or disables IGMP/MLD Snooping on a selected Vlan interface.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanGroupMembershipIn.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanGroupMembershipInterval
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanGroupMembershipIn.description: The amount of time in seconds that a switch will wait for a report from a particular group on the selected vlan before deleting the interface participating in the vlan from the entry. This value must be greater than agentSwitchIGMPSnoopingIntfMaxResponseTime.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMaxResponseTime.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMaxResponseTime
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMaxResponseTime.description: The amount of time in seconds a switch will wait after sending a query on the selected vlan because it did not receive a report for a particular group in the interface participating in the vlan. This value must be less than agentSwitchSnoopingIntfGroupMembershipInterval. The default value is 10. For IGMP & MLD Snooping this value ranges from 1 to 25.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanFastLeaveAdminMod.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanFastLeaveAdminMode
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanFastLeaveAdminMod.description: This enables or disables IGMP/MLD Snooping on the selected vlan.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMRPExpirationTime.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMRPExpirationTime
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMRPExpirationTime.description: The amount of time in seconds that a switch will wait for a query to be received on the selected interface participating in the vlan before the interface is removed from the list of interfaces with multicast routers attached. This parameter is configurable only for exisiting Vlans.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanReportSuppMode.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanReportSuppMode
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanReportSuppMode.description: This enables or disables IGMP/MLD Snooping Report Suppression feature on the selected vlan.

agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterTable.name: agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterTable
agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterTable.description: A table of the IGMP/MLD Static Mrouter Configuration parameters.

agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterEntry.name: agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterEntry
agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterEntry.description: Represents entry for a IGMP/MLD Static Mrouter.

agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterAdminMode.name: agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterAdminMode
agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterAdminMode.description: This enables or disables IGMP/MLD Mrouter on a per-interface per-vlan basis.

agentSwitchMFDBEntry.name: agentSwitchMFDBEntry
agentSwitchMFDBEntry.description: Contains Forwarding and Filtering information per Vlan Index, MAC Address, and Component User.

agentSwitchMFDBVlanId.name: agentSwitchMFDBVlanId
agentSwitchMFDBVlanId.description: Vlan Index for which this entry is associated with.

agentSwitchMFDBMacAddress.name: agentSwitchMFDBMacAddress
agentSwitchMFDBMacAddress.description: A multicast MAC address for which the switch has forwarding and or filtering information.

agentSwitchMFDBProtocolType.name: agentSwitchMFDBProtocolType
agentSwitchMFDBProtocolType.description: The component that is responsible for this entry in the Multicast Forwarding Database.

agentSwitchMFDBType.name: agentSwitchMFDBType
agentSwitchMFDBType.description: This displays the type of the entry. static(1) - Entries configured by the end user dynamic(2) - Entries added as a result of a learning process or protocol

agentSwitchMFDBDescription.name: agentSwitchMFDBDescription
agentSwitchMFDBDescription.description: Text description of this multicast table entry.

agentSwitchMFDBForwardingPortMask.name: agentSwitchMFDBForwardingPortMask
agentSwitchMFDBForwardingPortMask.description: BitMask indicating which ports this entry indicates should be forwarded. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table.

agentSwitchMFDBFilteringPortMask.name: agentSwitchMFDBFilteringPortMask
agentSwitchMFDBFilteringPortMask.description: BitMask indicating which ports this entry indicates should be filtered. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table.

agentSwitchMFDBSummaryTable.name: agentSwitchMFDBSummaryTable
agentSwitchMFDBSummaryTable.description: The Multicast Forwarding Database Summary table

agentSwitchMFDBSummaryEntry.name: agentSwitchMFDBSummaryEntry
agentSwitchMFDBSummaryEntry.description: Summarizes the forwarding ports for all components registered for all MFDB table entries with the same Vlan Index and MAC Address.

agentSwitchMFDBSummaryVlanId.name: agentSwitchMFDBSummaryVlanId
agentSwitchMFDBSummaryVlanId.description: Vlan Index for which this entry is associated with.

agentSwitchMFDBSummaryMacAddress.name: agentSwitchMFDBSummaryMacAddress
agentSwitchMFDBSummaryMacAddress.description: A multicast MAC address for which the switch has forwarding and or filtering information.

agentSwitchMFDBSummaryForwardingPortMask.name: agentSwitchMFDBSummaryForwardingPortMask
agentSwitchMFDBSummaryForwardingPortMask.description: Port Mask indicating which ports this entry indicates should be forwarded. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table.

agentSwitchMFDBMaxTableEntries.name: agentSwitchMFDBMaxTableEntries
agentSwitchMFDBMaxTableEntries.description: This displays the maximum number of entries that can possibly be in the Multicast Forwarding Database table.

agentSwitchMFDBMostEntriesUsed.name: agentSwitchMFDBMostEntriesUsed
agentSwitchMFDBMostEntriesUsed.description: This displays the largest number of entries that have been present in the Multicast Forwarding Database table. This value is also known as the MFDB high-water mark.

agentSwitchMFDBCurrentEntries.name: agentSwitchMFDBCurrentEntries
agentSwitchMFDBCurrentEntries.description: This displays the current number of entries in the Multicast Forwarding Database table.

agentSwitchDVlanTagEthertype.name: agentSwitchDVlanTagEthertype
agentSwitchDVlanTagEthertype.description: Configures the Double Vlan Tag Ethertype for the switch. If this object is supported, ethertype cannot be configured per port. Commonly used are the Ethertypes for vman tags (34984, or 0x88A8) and dot1q tags (33024, or 0x8100).

agentSwitchDVlanTagTable.name: agentSwitchDVlanTagTable
agentSwitchDVlanTagTable.description: A table of entries specifying the ethertype (TPID) values. This will let the user specify multiple ethertypes globally.

agentSwitchDVlanTagEntry.name: agentSwitchDVlanTagEntry
agentSwitchDVlanTagEntry.description: A table entry specifying the ethertype (TPID) values. Commonly used are the Ethertypes for vman tags (34984, or 0x88A8) and dot1q tags (33024, or 0x8100).

agentSwitchDVlanTagTPid.name: agentSwitchDVlanTagTPid
agentSwitchDVlanTagTPid.description: Ethertype value to identify incoming double tagged frames

agentSwitchDVlanTagPrimaryTPid.name: agentSwitchDVlanTagPrimaryTPid
agentSwitchDVlanTagPrimaryTPid.description: Specifies if this TPID is primary TPID for the switch or not

agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTable.name: agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTable
agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTable.description: A table entries specifying the ethertype (TPID) values per port.

agentSwitchPortDVlanTagEntry.name: agentSwitchPortDVlanTagEntry
agentSwitchPortDVlanTagEntry.description: A table entry specifying the ethertype (TPID) value for a port.

agentSwitchPortDVlanTagInterfaceIfIndex.name: agentSwitchPortDVlanTagInterfaceIfIndex
agentSwitchPortDVlanTagInterfaceIfIndex.description: Port Id on to which the Ethertype value is mapped

agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTPid.name: agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTPid
agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTPid.description: Ethertype value to identify incoming double tagged frames

agentSwitchPortDVlanTagMode.name: agentSwitchPortDVlanTagMode
agentSwitchPortDVlanTagMode.description: Controls the Double Vlan Tag mode on this port.

agentSwitchPortDVlanTagCustomerId.name: agentSwitchPortDVlanTagCustomerId
agentSwitchPortDVlanTagCustomerId.description: Configures the Customer ID for the Double Vlan Tag for this port.

agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationTable.name: agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationTable
agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationTable.description: The switch's MAC To VLAN association table

agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationEntry.name: agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationEntry
agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationEntry.description: VLAN to be assigned to untagged or priority tagged packets based on MAC address.

agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationVlanId.name: agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationVlanId
agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationVlanId.description: The VLAN the Mac address assigned to

agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationRowStatus.name: agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationRowStatus
agentSwitchVlanMacAssociationRowStatus.description: The Mac to VLAN association row status. Supported values: active(1) - valid entry createAndGo(4) - used to create a new entry destroy(6) - removes the entry

agentSwitchProtectedPortTable.name: agentSwitchProtectedPortTable
agentSwitchProtectedPortTable.description: The switch's protected port mapping table

agentSwitchProtectedPortGroupId.name: agentSwitchProtectedPortGroupId
agentSwitchProtectedPortGroupId.description: The group that this port belongs to

agentSwitchProtectedPortPortList.name: agentSwitchProtectedPortPortList
agentSwitchProtectedPortPortList.description: The set of ports that are protected in this group

agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationTable.name: agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationTable
agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationTable.description: The switch's Subnet To VLAN association table

agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationEntry.name: agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationEntry
agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationEntry.description: VLAN to be assigned to untagged or priority tagged packets based on IP address and Subnet Mask.

agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationVlanId.name: agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationVlanId
agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationVlanId.description: The VLAN that the IP address and subnet mask assigned to

agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationRowStatu.name: agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationRowStatus
agentSwitchVlanSubnetAssociationRowStatu.description: The Subnet to VLAN association row status. Supported values: active(1) - valid entry createAndGo(4) - used to create a new entry destroy(6) - removes the entry

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierCfgTable.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierCfgTable
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierCfgTable.description: A table of the IGMP/MLD Snooping Querier Global configuration entries.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierCfgEntry.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierCfgEntry
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierCfgEntry.description: Represents entry for Snooping Querier Configuration.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierAdminMode.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierAdminMode
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierAdminMode.description: This enables or disables Snooping Querier on the system.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVersion.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVersion
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVersion.description: This specifies the multicast protocol versions that are supported by the system.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierAddress.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierAddress
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierAddress.description: This specifies the default source ip address to be used while generating general queries.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierQueryInterval.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierQueryInterval
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierQueryInterval.description: This specified the timer interval after which the system generates general queries.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierExpiryInterval.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierExpiryInterval
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierExpiryInterval.description: This specified the timer interval after which the detected other querier information is no longer valid.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanTable.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanTable
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanTable.description: A table of the Snooping Querier Vlan configuration entries.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanEntry.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanEntry
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanEntry.description: Represents entry for a Snooping Querier configurable Vlan.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAdminMode.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAdminMode
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAdminMode.description: This enables or disables Snooping Querier on a selected Vlan interface.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanOperMode.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanOperMode
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanOperMode.description: This specifies the current state of the Snooping Querier on a selected vlan interface

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierElectionPartic.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierElectionParticipateMode
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierElectionPartic.description: This enables or disables the Snooping Querier Election Participation mode. When enabled snooping querier switch will participate in querier election up on discovering another querier in the specified vlan. When disabled, up on discovering another querier, snooping querier moves to non-querier state.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAddress.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAddress
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAddress.description: This specifies the default source ip address to be used while generating general queries on the specified vlan.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperVersion.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperVersion
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperVersion.description: This specifies the multicast protocol version that is currently being used by the snooping switch for the specified vlan while generating query messages.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperMaxRespons.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperMaxResponseTime
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperMaxRespons.description: The amount of time in seconds a switch will wait after sending a query on the selected vlan because it did not receive a report for a particular group in the interface participating in the vlan. This object is valid only when agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperVersion object is valid. (-1) - indicates that parameter is not available; ( 0) - indicates that response time is less then 1 second.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerierAdd.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerierAddress
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerierAdd.description: This specifies the last querier's ip address for the specified vlan. It represents the detected other multicast querier in the vlan.

agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerierVer.name: agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerierVersion
agentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerierVer.description: This specifies the multicast protocol version that is currently being used by the detected other multicast querier for the specified vlan. (-1) - indicates that parameter is not available.

agentSwitchVoiceVLANAdminMode.name: agentSwitchVoiceVLANAdminMode
agentSwitchVoiceVLANAdminMode.description: This enables or disables Voice VLAN on the system.

agentSwitchVoiceVlanDeviceTable.name: agentSwitchVoiceVlanDeviceTable
agentSwitchVoiceVlanDeviceTable.description: A table of the Voice Vlan device entries.

agentSwitchVoiceVlanDeviceEntry.name: agentSwitchVoiceVlanDeviceEntry
agentSwitchVoiceVlanDeviceEntry.description: Represents entry for a Voice Device on the interface.

agentSwitchVoiceVlanInterfaceNum.name: agentSwitchVoiceVlanInterfaceNum
agentSwitchVoiceVlanInterfaceNum.description: The interface number of this interface.

agentSwitchAddressConflictDetectionStatu.name: agentSwitchAddressConflictDetectionStatus
agentSwitchAddressConflictDetectionStatu.description: Displays if an address conflict was detected on the switch since the last reset of the status. Set to 'true' if detected, 'false' otherwise.

agentSwitchAddressConflictDetectionStatu.name: agentSwitchAddressConflictDetectionStatusReset
agentSwitchAddressConflictDetectionStatu.description: Clear the last address conflict detection status in the switch. A value of reset(1) is used to reset the status. A read on this object always returns the value none (0). The value none (0) cannot be forcibly set by the administrator.

agentSwitchLastConflictingIPAddr.name: agentSwitchLastConflictingIPAddr
agentSwitchLastConflictingIPAddr.description: The reported conflicting IP address on the switch since the last reset of the conflict detection status.

agentSwitchLastConflictingMacAddr.name: agentSwitchLastConflictingMacAddr
agentSwitchLastConflictingMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the host corresponding to the reported conflicting IP address on the switch since the last reset of the conflict detection status.

agentSwitchLastConflictReportedTime.name: agentSwitchLastConflictReportedTime
agentSwitchLastConflictReportedTime.description: Time since the last address conflict was detected. It is displayed in days, hours, minutes and seconds. It is set to a valid value only when the conflict detection status is 'true'.

agentSwitchConflictIPAddr.name: agentSwitchConflictIPAddr
agentSwitchConflictIPAddr.description: The IP address on the switch reported to have a conflict with another host's IP address.

agentSwitchConflictMacAddr.name: agentSwitchConflictMacAddr
agentSwitchConflictMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the host that has an IP address conflicting with the IP address on the switch.

agentSwitchAddressConflictDetectionRun.name: agentSwitchAddressConflictDetectionRun
agentSwitchAddressConflictDetectionRun.description: Trigger the action to run the active address conflict detection. A value of run(1) is used to issue the action command. A read on this object always returns the value none(0). The value none (0) cannot be forcibly set by the administrator.

agentTransferUploadMode.name: agentTransferUploadMode
agentTransferUploadMode.description: Transfer upload mode configures the mode to use when uploading from the switch. The mode is either X/Y/ZMODEM, TFTP, SFTP, FTP or SCP. X/Y/ZMODEM is valid only when the file transfer is initiated by the serial EIA 232 port. on the Linux platform. SFTP and SCP are only allowed if the SSH feature is present. Upload to USB is actual only if the USB feature is present.

agentTransferUploadServerIP.name: agentTransferUploadServerIP
agentTransferUploadServerIP.description: Transfer upload server ip configures the IP address of the server where the file is located. It is valid only when the Transfer Mode is TFTP, SFTP, or SCP. The address is 4 integer bytes ranging from 0 to 255. This object is deprecated in favour of agentTransferUploadServerAddress and agentTransferUploadServerAddressType.

agentTransferUploadPath.name: agentTransferUploadPath
agentTransferUploadPath.description: Transfer upload tftppath configures the directory path where the file is to be uploaded to. The switch remembers the last file path used.

agentTransferUploadFilename.name: agentTransferUploadFilename
agentTransferUploadFilename.description: Transfer upload tftpfilename configures the file name for the file being uploaded from the switch. It can be up to 32 alphanumeric characters. The switch remembers the last file name used. File path can be appended to the file name if the string is less than 17 characters. Otherwise, the File Path field will need to be used and the File Name will be appended to the File Path as is. An example would be File Path set to c:\tftp\code\ and File Name set to e1r1v1.opr. Note: File Name, File Path, and TFTP Server IP Address are applicable only if the Transfer Mode is TFTP.

agentTransferUploadDataType.name: agentTransferUploadDataType
agentTransferUploadDataType.description: Transfer upload datatype configures the type of file to upload from the switch. The types for upload are: - Code File - Configuration File - Operational log - Startup log

agentTransferUploadStart.name: agentTransferUploadStart
agentTransferUploadStart.description: Transfer upload start will start an upload transfer. The agentTransferUploadMode object must not be set to xmodem(2), ymodem(3), or zmodem(4) to initiate a transfer via SNMP.

agentTransferUploadStatus.name: agentTransferUploadStatus
agentTransferUploadStatus.description: Indicates the current status of an upload transfer.

agentTransferUploadServerAddressType.name: agentTransferUploadServerAddressType
agentTransferUploadServerAddressType.description: The type of the tftpserverip address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB. The agentTransferUploadServerAddress object is intepreted within the context of agentTransferUploadServerAddressType. Only ipv4(1) and ipv6(2) is supported at present.

agentTransferUploadServerAddress.name: agentTransferUploadServerAddress
agentTransferUploadServerAddress.description: Transfer upload tftpserverip configures the IP address of the server where the file is to be uploaded to.It is valid only when the Transfer Mode is TFTP, SFTP, FTP or SCP. The type of this address is determined by the value of the agentTransferUploadServerAddressType object. The values for agentTransferUploadServerAddressType and agentTransferUploadServerAddress must be consistent.

agentTransferUploadImagename.name: agentTransferUploadImagename
agentTransferUploadImagename.description: Transfer upload image name. Sets the image to be uploaded as the specified name. Imagename cannot be set to unknown(1) option. When no name is set this object returns unknown(1) by default. Note: Imagename, File Name, File Path, and Server IP Address are applicable only if the Transfer Mode is TFTP, SFTP, FTP or SCP.

agentTransferUploadUsername.name: agentTransferUploadUsername
agentTransferUploadUsername.description: Username applicable only to secure upload types, i.e., SFTP, FTP or SCP.

agentTransferUploadPassword.name: agentTransferUploadPassword
agentTransferUploadPassword.description: Password applicable only to secure upload types, i.e. SFTP, FTP or SCP.

agentTransferUploadRemoteFilename.name: agentTransferUploadRemoteFilename
agentTransferUploadRemoteFilename.description: Transfer upload remote filename configures the file name for the file being created remotely. It can be up to 32 alphanumeric characters. Note: File Name, File Path, and Server IP Address are applicable only if the Transfer Mode is TFTP, SFTP, FTP or SCP.

agentTransferDownloadMode.name: agentTransferDownloadMode
agentTransferDownloadMode.description: Transfer download mode configures the mode to use when downloading to the switch. The mode is either X/Y/ZMODEM, TFTP, SFTP, FTP or SCP. X/Y/ZMODEM is valid only when the file transfer is initiated by the serial EIA 232 port. Y/ZMODEM is valid only on the Linux platform. SFTP and SCP are only allowed if the SSH feature is present. Download to USB is only allowed if the USB feature is present.

agentTransferDownloadServerIP.name: agentTransferDownloadServerIP
agentTransferDownloadServerIP.description: Transfer download tftpserverip configures the IP address of the server where the file is located. It is valid only when the Transfer Mode is TFTP, SFTP or SCP. The address is 4 integer bytes ranging from 0 to 255. This object is deprecated in favour of agentTransferDownloadServerAddress and agentTransferDownloadServerAddressType.

agentTransferDownloadPath.name: agentTransferDownloadPath
agentTransferDownloadPath.description: Transfer download tftppath configures the directory path where the file is located. The switch remembers the last file path used.

agentTransferDownloadFilename.name: agentTransferDownloadFilename
agentTransferDownloadFilename.description: Transfer download tftpfilename configures the file name for the file being downloaded to the switch. It can be up to 32 alphanumeric characters. The switch remembers the last file name used. File path can be appended to the file name if the string is less than 33 characters. Otherwise, the File Path field will need to be used and the File Name will be appended to the File Path as is. An example would be File Path set to c:\tftp\code\ and File Name set to e1r1v1.opr. Note: Imagename, File Name, File Path, and TFTP Server IP Address are applicable only if the Transfer Mode is TFTP, SFTP, FTP or SCP and the object agentTransferDownloadDataType download type is not set to code.

agentTransferDownloadDataType.name: agentTransferDownloadDataType
agentTransferDownloadDataType.description: Transfer download datatype configures the type of file to download to the switch. The types for download are: code - Code File config-script - Configuration File sshkey-rsa1 - SSH-1 RSA Key File sshkey-rsa2 - SSH-2 RSA Key PEM File sshkey-dsa - SSH-2 DSA Key PEM File sslpem-root - SSL Trusted Root Certificate PEM File sslpem-server - SSL Server Certificate PEM File sslpem-dhweak - SSL DH Weak Encryption Parameter PEM File sslpem-dhstrong - SSL DH Strong Encryption Parameter PEM File ias-users - IAS user file Note: SSH Key files can only be downloaded if SSH Server is administratively disabled, and there are no active SSH sessions. Kernel file can be downloaded only on raptor platform and linux operating system.

agentTransferDownloadStart.name: agentTransferDownloadStart
agentTransferDownloadStart.description: Transfer download start will start an download transfer. The agentTransferDownloadMode object must not be set to xmodem(2), ymodem(3), or zmodem(4) to initiate a transfer via SNMP.

agentTransferDownloadStatus.name: agentTransferDownloadStatus
agentTransferDownloadStatus.description: Indicates the current status of an download transfer.

agentTransferDownloadServerAddressType.name: agentTransferDownloadServerAddressType
agentTransferDownloadServerAddressType.description: The type of the tftpserverip address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB. The agentTransferDownloadServerAddress object is intepreted within the context of agentTransferDownloadServerAddressType. Only ipv4(1) and ipv6(2) is supported at present.

agentTransferDownloadServerAddress.name: agentTransferDownloadServerAddress
agentTransferDownloadServerAddress.description: Transfer download tftpserverip configures the IP address of the server where the file is to be downloaded from.It is valid only when the Transfer Mode is TFTP, SFTP, FTP or SCP. The type of this address is determined by the value of the agentTransferDownloadServerAddressType object. The values for agentTransferDownloadServerAddressType and agentTransferDownloadServerAddress must be consistent.

agentTransferDownloadImagename.name: agentTransferDownloadImagename
agentTransferDownloadImagename.description: Transfer download image name. Sets the downloaded image as the specified name. Imagename cannot be set to unknown(1) option. When no name is set this object returns unknown(1) by default. Note: Imagename, File Name, File Path, and Server IP Address are applicable only if the Transfer Mode is TFTP, SFTP, FTP or SCP.

agentTransferDownloadUsername.name: agentTransferDownloadUsername
agentTransferDownloadUsername.description: Username applicable only to secure download types, i.e., SFTP, FTP or SCP.

agentTransferDownloadPassword.name: agentTransferDownloadPassword
agentTransferDownloadPassword.description: Password applicable only to secure download types, i.e. SFTP, FTP or SCP.

agentTransferDownloadRemoteFilename.name: agentTransferDownloadRemoteFilename
agentTransferDownloadRemoteFilename.description: Transfer download remote filename configures the file name for the file being transferred from remote system. It can be up to 31 alphanumeric characters.

agentActiveImage.name: agentActiveImage
agentActiveImage.description: The active image name. image1 or image2.

agentNextActiveImage.name: agentNextActiveImage
agentNextActiveImage.description: The next active image name. user assigns either image1 or image2.

agentActiveImageVersion.name: agentActiveImageVersion
agentActiveImageVersion.description: The software version of the active image.

agentBackupImageVersion.name: agentBackupImageVersion
agentBackupImageVersion.description: The software version of the backup image if present.

agentNextSelectedImage.name: agentNextSelectedImage
agentNextSelectedImage.description: The image selected for loading on next boot.

agentPortMirroringMode.name: agentPortMirroringMode
agentPortMirroringMode.description: Port mirroring mode: enable - enable mirroring mode disable - disable mirroring mode delete - clear MirroredPort and Probe Port configuration

agentPortMirrorTable.name: agentPortMirrorTable
agentPortMirrorTable.description: This table includes entries for each Port Mirroring session.

agentPortMirrorEntry.name: agentPortMirrorEntry
agentPortMirrorEntry.description: Provides configuration of a Port Mirroring session specifying the destination port, and the source Port Mask, providing a many-to-one mapping.

agentPortMirrorSessionNum.name: agentPortMirrorSessionNum
agentPortMirrorSessionNum.description: The Session number of this mirroring entry. The number of sessions is fixed, and is platform dependant.

agentPortMirrorDestinationPort.name: agentPortMirrorDestinationPort
agentPortMirrorDestinationPort.description: The port which traffic from the mirrored ports will be sent to.

agentPortMirrorSourcePortMask.name: agentPortMirrorSourcePortMask
agentPortMirrorSourcePortMask.description: The ports from which traffic will be sent to the destination port. The destination port can not be included in this list of ports.

agentPortMirrorAdminMode.name: agentPortMirrorAdminMode
agentPortMirrorAdminMode.description: The status of this port mirroring session. enable(1) - This session is active and all traffic from the source ports will be mirrored to the destination port. disable(2) - This session is not active. delete(3) - Remove the configuration for this Session

agentPortMirrorSourceVlan.name: agentPortMirrorSourceVlan
agentPortMirrorSourceVlan.description: The vlan from which traffic will be sent to the destination port.

agentPortMirrorRemoteSourceVlan.name: agentPortMirrorRemoteSourceVlan
agentPortMirrorRemoteSourceVlan.description: The remote vlan from which traffic will be sent to the destination port.

agentPortMirrorRemoteDestinationVlan.name: agentPortMirrorRemoteDestinationVlan
agentPortMirrorRemoteDestinationVlan.description: The VLAN that forwards the network traffic to the destination switch.

agentPortMirrorReflectorPort.name: agentPortMirrorReflectorPort
agentPortMirrorReflectorPort.description: The port to which traffic from the mirrored ports will be sent in case of destination being remote VLAN.

agentPortMirrorIpAccessListNumber.name: agentPortMirrorIpAccessListNumber
agentPortMirrorIpAccessListNumber.description: The IP access-list number attached to the port mirroring session.

agentPortMirrorMacAccessListNumber.name: agentPortMirrorMacAccessListNumber
agentPortMirrorMacAccessListNumber.description: The MAC access-list number attached to the port mirroring session.

agentPortMirrorTypeTable.name: agentPortMirrorTypeTable
agentPortMirrorTypeTable.description: This table includes entries for each source port's direction of port mirroring.

agentPortMirrorTypeEntry.name: agentPortMirrorTypeEntry
agentPortMirrorTypeEntry.description: Provides configuration of a Port Mirroring direction specifying the session of the port mirroring and source port

agentPortMirrorTypeSourcePort.name: agentPortMirrorTypeSourcePort
agentPortMirrorTypeSourcePort.description: The port from which traffic will be sent to the destination port. This port should be a source port in the corresponding session

agentPortMirrorTypeType.name: agentPortMirrorTypeType
agentPortMirrorTypeType.description: The direction of the data to be mirrored on this source port. tx(1) - The data that is transmitted from the source port. rx(2) - The data that is received on the source port. txrx(3) - The data that is transmitted/received from/on the source port

agentPortMirrorRemoteVlan.name: agentPortMirrorRemoteVlan
agentPortMirrorRemoteVlan.description: The VLAN configured as RSPAN VLAN.

agentPortMirrorRemoteVlanTable.name: agentPortMirrorRemoteVlanTable
agentPortMirrorRemoteVlanTable.description: A table of the RSPAN VLAN config entries

agentPortMirrorRemoteVlanIndex.name: agentPortMirrorRemoteVlanIndex
agentPortMirrorRemoteVlanIndex.description: The VLAN which is configured as a remote-span VLAN.

agentPortMirrorRemoteVlanRowStatus.name: agentPortMirrorRemoteVlanRowStatus
agentPortMirrorRemoteVlanRowStatus.description: The status of this entry. active(1) - the VLAN is configured as a remote-span VLAN createAndGo(4) - add the VLAN as a remote-span VLAN destroy(6) - remove the VLAN from the list of Remote-span VLAN. RSPAN VLAN cannot be removed or changed while it is used with a Monitor session.

agentDot3adAggPortTable.name: agentDot3adAggPortTable
agentDot3adAggPortTable.description: This table provides 802.3ad link aggregation information for each physical port that is not available through the standard MIB.

agentDot3adAggPortEntry.name: agentDot3adAggPortEntry
agentDot3adAggPortEntry.description: Information about a table entry. The agentDot3adAggPort identifies the external interface number of the port.

agentPortConfigTable.name: agentPortConfigTable
agentPortConfigTable.description: A table of the switch's physical port config entries

agentPortDot1dBasePort.name: agentPortDot1dBasePort
agentPortDot1dBasePort.description: The port number of this port.

agentPortSTPMode.name: agentPortSTPMode
agentPortSTPMode.description: The switch's Port Spanning Tree Protocol Mode STP mode values are: dot1d (the default) fast, indicates you want to use the fast spanning tree mode off, indicates the STP mode is turned off for a particular port This object is only supported when the Dot1d Protocol is enabled.

agentPortSTPState.name: agentPortSTPState
agentPortSTPState.description: The switch's Port Spanning Tree Protocol State. This object is only supported when the Dot1d Protocol is enabled.

agentPortPhysicalMode.name: agentPortPhysicalMode
agentPortPhysicalMode.description: The switch's Port Speed Mode. This is the configured physical mode. This object is read-only for gigabit ports

agentPortPhysicalStatus.name: agentPortPhysicalStatus
agentPortPhysicalStatus.description: The switch's Port Physical Speed Status. This is the current actual speed.

agentPortLinkTrapMode.name: agentPortLinkTrapMode
agentPortLinkTrapMode.description: If enabled, link up and link down traps will be sent for this port.

agentPortClearStats.name: agentPortClearStats
agentPortClearStats.description: clear stats for this port only

agentPortDefaultType.name: agentPortDefaultType
agentPortDefaultType.description: This object identifies the default administrative port type, to be used in conjunction with the operational port type denoted by agentPortType. The set of possible values for this object is the same as the set defined for the agentPortType object. This object represents the administratively-configured type of the MAU. If auto-negotiation is not enabled or is not implemented for this MAU, the value of this object determines the operational type of the MAU. In this case, a set to this object will force the MAU into the specified operating mode. If auto-negotiation is implemented and enabled for this MAU, the operational type of the MAU is determined by auto-negotiation, and the value of this object denotes the type to which the MAU will automatically revert if/when auto-negotiation is later disabled. The valid values for this object are: dot3MauType10BaseTHD dot3MauType10BaseTFD dot3MauType100BaseTXHD dot3MauType100BaseTXFD dot3MauType100BaseFXFD dot3MauType10GBaseSX

agentPortType.name: agentPortType
agentPortType.description: This object identifies the port type. An initial set of MAU types are defined in RFC 2668. The assignment of OBJECT IDENTIFIERs to new types of MAUs is managed by the IANA. If the MAU type is unknown, the object identifier unknownMauType OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } is returned. Note that unknownMauType is a syntactically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and the BER must be able to generate and recognize this value. This object represents the operational type of the MAU, as determined by either (1) the result of the auto-negotiation function or (2) if auto-negotiation is not enabled or is not implemented for this MAU, by the value of the object agentPortDefaultType, or (3) for the GigE card a value determined by the GBIC connected to the card. In case (2), a set to the object agentPortDefaultType will force the MAU into the new operating mode. The valid values for this object are: dot3MauType10BaseTHD dot3MauType10BaseTFD dot3MauType100BaseTXHD dot3MauType100BaseTXFD dot3MauType100BaseFXFD dot3MauType1000BaseSXFD dot3MauType10GBaseSX

agentPortAutoNegAdminStatus.name: agentPortAutoNegAdminStatus
agentPortAutoNegAdminStatus.description: This object identifies the administration status of auto negotiation for this port.

agentPortDot3FlowControlMode.name: agentPortDot3FlowControlMode
agentPortDot3FlowControlMode.description: Config flowcontrol allows you to enable or disable 802.3x flow control for this port. This value applies to only full-duplex mode ports. Enabling asymmetric flow control allows the port to receive pause frames but it will not transmit pause frames.

agentPortDVlanTagMode.name: agentPortDVlanTagMode
agentPortDVlanTagMode.description: Controls the Double Vlan Tag mode on this port.

agentPortDVlanTagEthertype.name: agentPortDVlanTagEthertype
agentPortDVlanTagEthertype.description: Configures the Double Vlan Tag Ethertype for this port. If this object is supported, ethertype cannot be configured globally for the switch. Commonly used are the Ethertypes for vman tags (34984, or 0x88A8) and dot1q tags (33024, or 0x8100).

agentPortDVlanTagCustomerId.name: agentPortDVlanTagCustomerId
agentPortDVlanTagCustomerId.description: Configures the Customer ID for the Double Vlan Tag for this port.

agentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit.name: agentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit
agentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit.description: This object identifies the largest value that can be configured for agentPortMaxFrameSize

agentPortMaxFrameSize.name: agentPortMaxFrameSize
agentPortMaxFrameSize.description: This object identifies the currently configured maximum frame size value for this port. The maximmum value that this object can be set to is the value of agentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit. For Ethernet ports which support 802.1Q vlan tagging, the minimum value that this object can be set to is 1522

agentPortBroadcastControlMode.name: agentPortBroadcastControlMode
agentPortBroadcastControlMode.description: If enabled, broadcast storm recovery will function on this port. When you specify Enable for Broadcast Storm Recovery and the broadcast traffic on this Ethernet port exceeds the configured threshold, the switch blocks (discards) the broadcast traffic.

agentPortBroadcastControlThreshold.name: agentPortBroadcastControlThreshold
agentPortBroadcastControlThreshold.description: Configures the broadcast storm recovery threshold for this port.

agentPortMulticastControlMode.name: agentPortMulticastControlMode
agentPortMulticastControlMode.description: If enabled, multicast storm recovery will function on this port. When you specify Enable for Multicast Storm Recovery and the multicast traffic on this Ethernet port exceeds the configured threshold, the switch blocks (discards) the multicast traffic.

agentPortMulticastControlThreshold.name: agentPortMulticastControlThreshold
agentPortMulticastControlThreshold.description: Configures the multicast storm recovery threshold for this port.

agentPortUnicastControlMode.name: agentPortUnicastControlMode
agentPortUnicastControlMode.description: If enabled, unicast storm recovery will function on this port. When you specify Enable for Unicast Storm Recovery and the unknown unicast traffic on this Ethernet port exceeds the configured threshold, the switch blocks (discards) the unknown unicast traffic.

agentPortUnicastControlThreshold.name: agentPortUnicastControlThreshold
agentPortUnicastControlThreshold.description: Configures the unicast storm recovery threshold for this port.

agentPortVoiceVlanMode.name: agentPortVoiceVlanMode
agentPortVoiceVlanMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Mode.

agentPortVoiceVlanID.name: agentPortVoiceVlanID
agentPortVoiceVlanID.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN ID if the Voice Vlan Mode is Vlan ID.

agentPortVoiceVlanPriority.name: agentPortVoiceVlanPriority
agentPortVoiceVlanPriority.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Priority if the Voice Vlan Mode is dot1p. A value of 255 indicates that the priority is not configured.

agentPortVoiceVlanDataPriorityMode.name: agentPortVoiceVlanDataPriorityMode
agentPortVoiceVlanDataPriorityMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Data Priority Mode.

agentPortVoiceVlanOperationalStatus.name: agentPortVoiceVlanOperationalStatus
agentPortVoiceVlanOperationalStatus.description: Describes the Port Voice VLAN Operational Status.

agentPortVoiceVlanAuthenticationMode.name: agentPortVoiceVlanAuthenticationMode
agentPortVoiceVlanAuthenticationMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Authentication Mode. It is enabled by default. To disable, following are the pre-requisites. Voice Vlan shall be enabled Globally, Dot1x Admin Mode shall be enabled, Dot1x port-control shall be mac-based, and the port is required to be in General Mode.

agentPortDot3FlowControlOperStatus.name: agentPortDot3FlowControlOperStatus
agentPortDot3FlowControlOperStatus.description: This object identifies operational status of the flow control per port.

agentPortTransceiverFwPartNumber.name: agentPortTransceiverFwPartNumber
agentPortTransceiverFwPartNumber.description: Firmware part number of 10GBASE-T transceiver. For other ports, or if module is not inserted, octet sting will be filled with 0xFF bytes. See also next field, agentPortTransceiverFwRevision. PN is an 8-byte field that contains ASCII characters, left-aligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces (0x20). A field value of all zeros indicates that PN is unspecified.

agentPortTransceiverFwRevision.name: agentPortTransceiverFwRevision
agentPortTransceiverFwRevision.description: Firmware revision of 10GBASE-T transceiver. For other ports, or if module is not inserted, octet sting will be filled with 0xFF bytes. See also previous field, PortTransceiverFwPartNumber. Rev is a 16-byte field that contains ASCII characters, left-aligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces (0x20). A field value of all zeros indicates that Rev is unspecified.

agentPortBroadcastControlThresholdUnit.name: agentPortBroadcastControlThresholdUnit
agentPortBroadcastControlThresholdUnit.description: Configures the units of the threshold value to percentage of port speed or absolute packets per second.

agentPortMulticastControlThresholdUnit.name: agentPortMulticastControlThresholdUnit
agentPortMulticastControlThresholdUnit.description: Configures the units of the threshold value to percentage of port speed or absolute packets per second.

agentPortUnicastControlThresholdUnit.name: agentPortUnicastControlThresholdUnit
agentPortUnicastControlThresholdUnit.description: Configures the units of the threshold value to percentage of port speed or absolute packets per second.

agentPortVoiceVlanUntagged.name: agentPortVoiceVlanUntagged
agentPortVoiceVlanUntagged.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN tagging mode.

agentPortVoiceVlanNoneMode.name: agentPortVoiceVlanNoneMode
agentPortVoiceVlanNoneMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN None mode.

agentPortSpeedDuplexStatus.description: This object is used to set the speed and duplex settings for a port. If auto-duplex(0) or speed-auto(3) is enabled, then auto-negotiation is enabled.If auto-duplex(0) is set but speed-auto(3) is not set, then the admin advertisements will be limited to the speed values enabled. agentPortNativeVlanID.name: agentPortNativeVlanID
agentPortNativeVlanID.description: Describes and Configures the VLAN ID of Trunk switch port. Configures the Native VLAN Id for the port.

agentPortDDisableAutorecoveryTime.name: agentPortDDisableAutorecoveryTime
agentPortDDisableAutorecoveryTime.description: The time in seconds left to port autorecovery from D-Disable state.

agentPortDDisableComponents.name: agentPortDDisableComponents
agentPortDDisableComponents.description: The list of components put the port to D-Disable state.

agentPortLoadStatsInterval.name: agentPortLoadStatsInterval
agentPortLoadStatsInterval.description: The length of time for which data is used to compute load statistics. The value is given in seconds, and must be a multiple of 30. The allowable range is 30 to 600 seconds.

agentStpPortState.description: The administrative STP state for the port. enable(1) - enables STP on the port. disable(2) - disables STP on the port. The default port STP state is enabled for the first 4095 ports and disabled for any ports beyond.

agentStpPortStatsMstpBpduTx.description: The MSTP BPDUs sent from a specific port.

agentStpPortStatsRstpBpduRx.description: The RSTP BPDUs received on a specific port.

agentStpPortStatsRstpBpduTx.description: The RSTP BPDUs sent from a specific port.

agentStpPortStatsStpBpduRx.description: The STP BPDUs received on a specific port.

agentStpPortStatsStpBpduTx.description: The STP BPDUs sent from a specific port.

agentStpPortUpTime.description: Time since port was reset. It is displayed in days, hours, minutes, and seconds.

agentStpPortMigrationCheck.description: Force the specified port to transmit RSTP or MSTP BPDU's. Supported values: false(0) - BPDUs are not to be transmitted. true(1) - BPDUs are to be transmitted A non-zero value indicates that BPDUs are to be sent on the specified port.

agentStpPortRootGuard.name: agentStpPortRootGuard
agentStpPortRootGuard.description: Manage root-guard on the specified interface. Supported values: false(0) - Root-guard is disabled. true(1) - Root-guard is enabled.

agentStpCstHelloTime.name: agentStpCstHelloTime
agentStpCstHelloTime.description: The MSTP root port hello time for the CIST.

agentStpCstMaxAge.name: agentStpCstMaxAge
agentStpCstMaxAge.description: The MSTP root port max age for the CIST.

agentStpCstRegionalRootId.name: agentStpCstRegionalRootId
agentStpCstRegionalRootId.description: The MSTP regional root identifier for the CIST.

agentStpCstRegionalRootPathCost.name: agentStpCstRegionalRootPathCost
agentStpCstRegionalRootPathCost.description: The MSTP regional root path cost for the CIST.

agentStpCstRootFwdDelay.name: agentStpCstRootFwdDelay
agentStpCstRootFwdDelay.description: The MSTP root port forward delay for the CIST.

agentStpCstBridgeFwdDelay.name: agentStpCstBridgeFwdDelay
agentStpCstBridgeFwdDelay.description: The MSTP bridge forward delay for the CIST. The default value is 15. This value must be >= ((MSTP root port max age/2) + 1).

agentStpCstBridgeHelloTime.name: agentStpCstBridgeHelloTime
agentStpCstBridgeHelloTime.description: The MSTP bridge hello time for the CIST. The default value is 2.According to IEEE 802.1Q-REV 2005 updating hello time is disallowed

agentStpCstBridgeHoldTime.name: agentStpCstBridgeHoldTime
agentStpCstBridgeHoldTime.description: The MSTP bridge hold time for the CIST.

agentStpCstBridgeMaxAge.name: agentStpCstBridgeMaxAge
agentStpCstBridgeMaxAge.description: The MSTP bridge max age for the CIST. The default value is 20.

agentStpCstBridgeMaxHops.name: agentStpCstBridgeMaxHops
agentStpCstBridgeMaxHops.description: The MSTP bridge max hops for the CIST. The default value is 20.

agentStpCstBridgePriority.name: agentStpCstBridgePriority
agentStpCstBridgePriority.description: The MSTP bridge priority for the CIST. The default value is 32768.

agentStpCstBridgeHoldCount.name: agentStpCstBridgeHoldCount
agentStpCstBridgeHoldCount.description: The MSTP bridge hold count for the CIST. This command sets the value of maximum bpdus that a bridge is allowed to send within a hello time window. The default value is 6.

agentStpCstPortOperEdge.name: agentStpCstPortOperEdge
agentStpCstPortOperEdge.description: The MSTP operational status of a specific port for the CIST.

agentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint.name: agentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint
agentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint.description: The MSTP operational point to point mac of a specific port for the CIST.

agentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck.name: agentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck
agentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck.description: The MSTP topology change acknowledge for a specific port in the CIST.

agentStpCstPortEdge.name: agentStpCstPortEdge
agentStpCstPortEdge.description: The administrative state of a specific port in CIST. enable(1) - enables the port. disable(2) - disables the port. The default port state is disabled. For the M6220, the default port state is enabled for internal ports and disabled for external ports.

agentStpCstPortForwardingState.name: agentStpCstPortForwardingState
agentStpCstPortForwardingState.description: The MSTP forwarding state of a specific port in CIST.

agentStpCstPortId.name: agentStpCstPortId
agentStpCstPortId.description: The MSTP port identifier of a specific port in CIST.

agentStpCstPortPathCost.name: agentStpCstPortPathCost
agentStpCstPortPathCost.description: The MSTP port path cost in CIST. The default value will correspond to the recommendation specified in IEEE 802.1s Table 13-2 which varies depending upon link speed.

agentStpCstPortPriority.name: agentStpCstPortPriority
agentStpCstPortPriority.description: The MSTP port priority in CIST. The priority is in the increments of 16. The default value is 128.

agentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId.name: agentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId
agentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId.description: The MSTP designated bridge ID of a specific port in CIST.

agentStpCstDesignatedCost.name: agentStpCstDesignatedCost
agentStpCstDesignatedCost.description: The MSTP designated cost of a specific port in CIST.

agentStpCstDesignatedPortId.name: agentStpCstDesignatedPortId
agentStpCstDesignatedPortId.description: The MSTP designated port ID of a specific port in CIST.

agentStpCstExtPortPathCost.name: agentStpCstExtPortPathCost
agentStpCstExtPortPathCost.description: The MSTP external port path cost in CIST. The default value varies depending upon the link speed.

agentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect.name: agentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect
agentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect.description: BPDU Guard Mode effect on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Guard Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Guard Mode is disabled on the port.

agentStpCstPortBpduFilter.name: agentStpCstPortBpduFilter
agentStpCstPortBpduFilter.description: This command sets BPDU Filter mode on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Filter Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Filter Mode is disabled on the port.

agentStpCstPortBpduFlood.name: agentStpCstPortBpduFlood
agentStpCstPortBpduFlood.description: This command sets BPDU Flood mode on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Flood Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Flood Mode is disabled on the port.

agentStpCstPortAutoEdge.name: agentStpCstPortAutoEdge
agentStpCstPortAutoEdge.description: This command sets the auto-edge mode of the port which enables it to become an edge port if it does not see BPDUs for some duration. enable(1) - enables the auto-edge mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the auto-edge mode for the port. The default auto-edge mode is disabled.

agentStpCstPortRootGuard.name: agentStpCstPortRootGuard
agentStpCstPortRootGuard.description: This command sets a port to discard any superior information received by the port and thus protect against root of the device from changing.The port gets put into discarding state and does not forward any packets. enable(1) - enables the root-guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the root-guard mode for the port. The default root-guard mode is disabled.

agentStpCstPortTCNGuard.name: agentStpCstPortTCNGuard
agentStpCstPortTCNGuard.description: This command restricts the port from propagating any topology change information received through that port. enable(1) - enables the tcn-guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the tcn-guard mode for the port. The default tcn-guard mode is disabled.

agentStpCstPortLoopGuard.name: agentStpCstPortLoopGuard
agentStpCstPortLoopGuard.description: This command enables loop guard on this port. This setting applies to all Spanning Tree instances of which this port is a member. enable(1) - enables the loop guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the loop guard mode for the port. The default loop-guard mode is disabled.

agentStpMstBridgePriority.name: agentStpMstBridgePriority
agentStpMstBridgePriority.description: The MSTP bridge priority in a specific instance. The priority is in the increments of 4096. The recommended default value is 32768.

agentStpMstBridgeIdentifier.name: agentStpMstBridgeIdentifier
agentStpMstBridgeIdentifier.description: The MSTP bridge identifier in a specific instance.

agentStpMstDesignatedRootId.name: agentStpMstDesignatedRootId
agentStpMstDesignatedRootId.description: The MSTP designated root bridge identifier in a specific instance.

agentStpMstRootPortId.description: The MSTP root port ID in a specific instance.

agentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: agentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange
agentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The MSTP time since the last topology change in a specific instance.

agentStpMstTopologyChangeCount.name: agentStpMstTopologyChangeCount
agentStpMstTopologyChangeCount.description: The MSTP count of topology changes in a specific instance.

agentStpMstTopologyChangeParm.name: agentStpMstTopologyChangeParm
agentStpMstTopologyChangeParm.description: The MSTP topology change parameter in a specific instance.

agentStpMstRowStatus.description: The MSTP instance status. Supported values: active(1) - valid instance. createAndGo(4) - used to create a new instance. destroy(6) - removes an instance.

agentStpMstDesignatedPortId.description: The MSTP designated port ID of a specific port in a specific instance.
